The paper presents a framework for end-to-end learning of knowledge base representations using neural representation learning and probabilistic models. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) due to the use of neural networks, as well as Databases (cs.DB) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) due to the focus on knowledge base completion. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of relational and numerical features, which could also suggest Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as a possible sub-category.
